<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 07 at 7:14PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Roosevelt, east central Valley and northwestern McCone Counties
through 815 PM MDT...
At 713 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Nashua, or 17 miles southeast of Glasgow, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Wolf Point, Nashua, Frazer and Oswego.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
